FIFA World Cup Match Insights
Comprehensive Analysis of FIFA World Cup Matches (1930–2022)

This repository contains an end‑to‑end analysis of the FIFA World Cup Match Insights dataset sourced from Kaggle. It includes data exploration, performance metrics, match statistics, and visual dashboards summarizing 90+ years of World Cup history.

Dataset Source:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/saadaliyaseen/fifa-world-cup-match-insights
Project Overview
This project analyzes historical FIFA World Cup match data to uncover trends in:

Total goals scored

Match outcomes (home wins, away wins, draws)

Goal differences

Win percentages

Team‑wise performance

Stage‑wise match statistics

The analysis is supported by visual dashboards similar to the ones shown in the included PDF (Power BI report).
 Key Insights
 Total Goals & Match Stats
2,414 total goals scored across all matches

837 total matches analyzed

2.88 average goals per match

Match Outcomes
488 home wins

174 away wins

3910 draws (as shown in dashboard visuals)

 Additional Metrics
672 goal difference (aggregate)

79.09% win percentage (team‑level metric from dashboard)

What This Project Covers
Data Cleaning & Preparation
Handling missing values

Standardizing team names

Converting match dates

Extracting tournament stages

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
Distribution of goals

Match outcome patterns

Team‑wise scoring trends

Stage‑wise performance

 Visual Dashboards (Power BI)
(https://github.com/karthic180/power-bi-dashboards/blob/main/worldcup%20pbi.pdf) 
The included PDF contains dashboards such as:

Match Performance Overview

Team Insights

Goals & Outcomes Summary

Stage‑wise Match Breakdown

Tools & Technologies
Python (Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Seaborn)	for Data cleaning & analysis
Power BI	for Interactive dashboards
Jupyter Notebook	for Exploratory analysis
Kaggle Dataset as	Data source

